title: $:/plugins/BurningTreeC/minimap/ui/ControlPanel
tags: $:/tags/ControlPanel/SettingsTab
caption: Minimap

! Minimap Settings

A vertically-scaled overview of the story river, in the style of the CodeMirror&nbsp;6 minimap.

!! Display

<$checkbox tiddler="$:/config/BurningTreeC/minimap/enabled" field="text" checked="yes" unchecked="no" default="yes"> ''Show minimap'' — also toggled by the arrow button in the top-right bar</$checkbox>

!! Width

The width of the minimap in pixels (the story river and sidebar make room for it automatically):

<$range tiddler="$:/config/BurningTreeC/minimap/width" min="60" max="320" increment="10" default="120"/> <$text text={{{ [{$:/config/BurningTreeC/minimap/width}addsuffix[px]] }}}/>

!! Appearance

Border drawn around each tiddler in the minimap, for visibility:

<$select tiddler="$:/config/BurningTreeC/minimap/block-border" default="1">
<option value="0">None</option>
<option value="1">Subtle (1px)</option>
<option value="2">Distinct (2px)</option>
<option value="3">Strong (3px)</option>
</$select>

!! Tooltips

<$checkbox tiddler="$:/config/BurningTreeC/minimap/tooltips" field="text" checked="yes" unchecked="no" default="no"> ''Show tooltips'' — hovering a tiddler in the minimap shows its title</$checkbox>

!! Embed thumbnails

Embedded videos, tracks and pens (YouTube, Vimeo, Spotify, SoundCloud, Dailymotion, CodePen, CodeSandbox, Internet Archive) show a preview thumbnail in the minimap automatically.

<$checkbox tiddler="$:/config/BurningTreeC/minimap/apple-music" field="text" checked="yes" unchecked="no" default="no"> ''Apple Music thumbnails''</$checkbox>

<div style="opacity:0.7;font-size:0.85em;">Off by default. Apple's artwork lookup has no CORS, so previews can only be fetched via JSONP, which loads a script from `itunes.apple.com`. The request is built entirely by the plugin (fixed host, numeric album id), but enabling it means trusting that endpoint to run script in your wiki. Leave off if your wiki uses a strict Content-Security-Policy.</div>
